Alexei Miller von Gazprom calls pipeline in Bulgaria beginning of a new gas era
The commencement of construction of the South stream pipeline in Bulgaria represents the start one of the largest European energy projects, explained the Gazprom executive committee.
„The today's event is a milestone: The construction work at the Bulgarian section of the South stream gas pipeline, the largest and most important project in Europe, began”, said the chairman of the board of Gazprom, Alexei Miller, on Thursday in an explanation.
The project is a key element for the energy security of the entire European continent.
South Stream is to provide for more varieties with of Russia export routes by Europe.
A contract dispute between Gazprom and its counterparts in the Ukraine, in which the majority of the Russian gas for Europe is stored, provides for a increased risk with conventional routes, as is to be heard from official side to.
Miller said, which means direct connection to Bulgaria, a member of the European union, that the geopolitical risks linked with transit countries are switched off „always”.
Bulgarian consumers receive gas from South Stream to vergünstigten tariffs, if the entire project goes 2015 into enterprise.
According to Gazprom the construction work in other subordinate countries on the planned route is to begin to the end of the year.
The pipeline is appropriate for an annual capacity of 62.3 billion cubic meters natural gas.
